Secretary of Energy Jennifer Granholm joined the White House press briefing to discuss the Biden administration's goals for clean energy and job creation. Secretary Granholm emphasized the importance of investing in clean energy technologies and infrastructure to reduce greenhouse gas emissions and create good-paying union jobs. She highlighted her experience as governor of Michigan, where she successfully diversified the state's economy and promoted the growth of clean energy industries. Secretary Granholm also discussed the global market for clean energy products and the need for the United States to compete in this market. She stressed the importance of bipartisan support for the American Jobs Plan, which includes funding for clean energy research and development, infrastructure, and job creation. Secretary Granholm also addressed questions about nuclear energy and the storage of nuclear waste, as well as the role of the federal government in ensuring that clean energy jobs are high-paying and have benefits.